<div class="container">
    <h1 style="color: var(--text-color);">Daily Plan: Friday, January 9, 2026 (Week 2 Kickoff: C.2 Model Audit + F.1 IDE Integration)</h1>
    
    <div class="last-updated" style="color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
        <strong>Context:</strong> First day of Week 2 | 
        <strong>Status:</strong> 3 Priority Tasks | 
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> 2026-01-09
    </div>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p><strong>Objectives:</strong> Continue C.2 Model Audit (70+ models catalogued), launch F.1 Master Plan IDE Integration work, review Week 1 accomplishments and blockers.</p>
    <p><strong>Week Context:</strong> Week 1 (Jan 2-8) focused on critical infrastructure (A.2 K8s Readiness, A.3 Credentials Audit, B.1-B.3 bug fixes). Week 2 shifts focus to foundational audits (C.1-C.3) and coordination infrastructure (F.1). F.1 work enables all other plans by improving team workflow and tracking.</p>

    <h2>🔴 Priority 1: C.2 Model Audit - Continuation (3-4 hours)</h2>
    
    <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; padding: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #ff6b6b; margin: 15px 0;">
        <h3 style="color: #d9534f; margin-top: 0;">Strategic Audit: Database Model Catalog</h3>
        <p><strong>Master Plan Reference:</strong> C.2 in Priority Matrix - MEDIUM importance, HIGH effort, STRATEGIC initiative. Database contains 70+ models. Audit will create foundation for code generation and future enhancements.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Task: Model Documentation Progress (Continuation)</h3>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Continue from Jan 8 progress:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Review: Which models were documented on Jan 8</li>
                <li>Continue: With next tier of models (Project, Todo, Site, Theme models)</li>
                <li>Document: Database schema, relationships, foreign keys, validation rules</li>
                <li>Create: One .tt documentation file per model group</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Model documentation template:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>File: /Documentation/Models/[ModelName]_Model.tt</li>
                <li>Sections: Overview, Database Schema (columns, types, constraints), Relationships, Validation Rules, Usage Examples, Related Controllers</li>
                <li>Format: Use documentation_tt_template.tt as base</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Track audit progress:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Update: C2_Model_Audit_Plan.tt with count of documented models (target: 15+ by end of day)</li>
                <li>Create: Models_Documentation_Index.tt linking all created model docs</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>
    <p><strong>Expected Deliverable:</strong> 12-15 model documentation files + updated audit status</p>
    <p><strong>Time Estimate:</strong> 3-4 hours | <strong>Success Criteria:</strong> Critical models documented + audit progress >30% complete</p>

    <h2>🟠 Priority 2: F.1 Master Plan IDE Integration - Launch (2-3 hours)</h2>
    
    <div style="background-color: #e8f4f8; padding: 15px; border-left: 4px solid #0c5460; margin: 15px 0;">
        <h3 style="color: #0c5460; margin-top: 0;">Strategic Initiative: Master Plan IDE Integration</h3>
        <p><strong>Master Plan Reference:</strong> F.1 in Priority Matrix - HIGH importance, MEDIUM effort, STRATEGIC initiative. Enables team workflow improvements by integrating master plan with IDE-based project management. Multiplies effectiveness of all other plans.</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Task: F.1 Architecture & Environment Prep</h3>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Review F.1 requirements:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Read: F.1_Master_Plan_IDE_Integration.tt specification</li>
                <li>Understand: Required IDE integrations (PyCharm, VS Code plugins)</li>
                <li>Plan: Phased approach (Phase 1: IDE project integration, Phase 2: Workflow automation)</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Setup development environment:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Install: Required IDE plugins/extensions (if not already available)</li>
                <li>Configure: IDE project settings for team workflow</li>
                <li>Create: IDE configuration documentation for team setup</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Phase 1 design document:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Create: /Documentation/F1_IDE_Integration_Phase1_Design.tt</li>
                <li>Include: IDE integration architecture, team workflow diagram, required plugins, configuration checklist</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>
    <p><strong>Expected Deliverable:</strong> F.1 Phase 1 design document + IDE environment setup complete</p>
    <p><strong>Time Estimate:</strong> 2-3 hours | <strong>Success Criteria:</strong> Design complete + team can begin IDE integration testing</p>

    <h2>🟡 Priority 3: Week 1 Results Review & Week 2 Blockers (1 hour)</h2>
    
    <h3>Task: Audit Week 1 for Blockers & Dependencies</h3>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Review Week 1 completion summary:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Open: Daily_Plans-2026-01-08.tt and review completion results</li>
                <li>Document: What was completed, what was deferred, what blockers emerged</li>
                <li>Identify: Any infrastructure issues needing immediate attention</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Update master plan with Week 2 sequence:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Read: MASTER_PLAN_COORDINATION.tt for Week 2 recommended sequence</li>
                <li>Adjust: C.2, C.3, F.1 timing based on Week 1 results</li>
                <li>Note: Any dependencies that should be prioritized differently</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Prepare for escalation if needed:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Document: Any critical blockers that need architecture review</li>
                <li>Flag: Dependencies that would impact Week 2 timeline</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>

